     9Ôćĺ# Mitt
    11Ôćĺ> Tiny 200b functional event emitter / pubsub.
    12Ôćĺ
    13Ôćĺ-   **Microscopic:** weighs less than 200 bytes gzipped
    14Ôćĺ-   **Useful:** a wildcard `"*"` event type listens to all events
    15Ôćĺ-   **Familiar:** same names & ideas as [Node's EventEmitter](https://nodejs.org/api/events.html#events_class_eventemitter)
    16Ôćĺ-   **Functional:** methods don't rely on `this`
    17Ôćĺ-   **Great Name:** somehow [mitt](https://npm.im/mitt) wasn't taken
    18Ôćĺ
    19ÔćĺMitt was made for the browser, but works in any JavaScript runtime. It has no dependencies and supports IE9+.
    20Ôćĺ
    21Ôćĺ## Table of Contents
    23Ôćĺ-   [Install](#install)
    24Ôćĺ-   [Usage](#usage)
    25Ôćĺ-   [Examples & Demos](#examples--demos)
    26Ôćĺ-   [API](#api)
    27Ôćĺ-   [Contribute](#contribute)
    28Ôćĺ-   [License](#license)
    29Ôćĺ
    30Ôćĺ## Install
    32ÔćĺThis project uses [node](http://nodejs.org) and [npm](https://npmjs.com). Go check them out if you don't have them locally installed.
    33Ôćĺ
    34Ôćĺ```sh
    35Ôćĺ$ npm install --save mitt
    36Ôćĺ```
    37Ôćĺ
    38ÔćĺThen with a module bundler like [rollup](http://rollupjs.org/) or [webpack](https://webpack.js.org/), use as you would anything else:
    39Ôćĺ
    40Ôćĺ```javascript
    41Ôćĺ// using ES6 modules
    42Ôćĺimport mitt from 'mitt'
    43Ôćĺ
    44Ôćĺ// using CommonJS modules
    45Ôćĺvar mitt = require('mitt')
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    56Ôćĺ## Usage
    58Ôćĺ```js
    59Ôćĺimport mitt from 'mitt'
    60Ôćĺ
    61Ôćĺconst emitter = mitt()
    62Ôćĺ
    63Ôćĺ// listen to an event
    64Ôćĺemitter.on('foo', e => console.log('foo', e) )
    65Ôćĺ
    66Ôćĺ// listen to all events
    67Ôćĺemitter.on('*', (type, e) => console.log(type, e) )
    68Ôćĺ
    69Ôćĺ// fire an event
    70Ôćĺemitter.emit('foo', { a: 'b' })
    71Ôćĺ
      ÔćĺÔÇŽ
    81Ôćĺ### Typescript
    83ÔćĺSet `"strict": true` in your tsconfig.json to get improved type inference for `mitt` instance methods.
    84Ôćĺ
    85Ôćĺ```ts
    86Ôćĺimport mitt from 'mitt';
    87Ôćĺ
    88Ôćĺtype Events = {
    89Ôćĺ  foo: string;
    90Ôćĺ  bar?: number;
    91Ôćĺ};
    92Ôćĺ
    93Ôćĺconst emitter = mitt<Events>(); // inferred as Emitter<Events>
    94Ôćĺ
    95Ôćĺemitter.on('foo', (e) => {}); // 'e' has inferred type 'string'
    96Ôćĺ
