   138Ôćĺ### mitt
   140ÔćĺMitt: Tiny (~200b) functional event emitter / pubsub.
   141Ôćĺ
   142ÔćĺReturns **Mitt** 
   143Ôćĺ
   144Ôćĺ### all
   146ÔćĺA Map of event names to registered handler functions.
   147Ôćĺ
   148Ôćĺ### on
   150ÔćĺRegister an event handler for the given type.
   151Ôćĺ
   152Ôćĺ#### Parameters
   154Ôćĺ-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** Type of event to listen for, or `'*'` for all events
   155Ôćĺ-   `handler` **[Function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)** Function to call in response to given event
   156Ôćĺ
   157Ôćĺ### off
   159ÔćĺRemove an event handler for the given type.
   160ÔćĺIf `handler` is omitted, all handlers of the given type are removed.
   161Ôćĺ
   162Ôćĺ#### Parameters
   164Ôćĺ-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** Type of event to unregister `handler` from, or `'*'`
   165Ôćĺ-   `handler` **[Function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)?** Handler function to remove
   166Ôćĺ
   167Ôćĺ### emit
   169ÔćĺInvoke all handlers for the given type.
   170ÔćĺIf present, `'*'` handlers are invoked after type-matched handlers.
   171Ôćĺ
   172ÔćĺNote: Manually firing '\*' handlers is not supported.
   173Ôćĺ
   174Ôćĺ#### Parameters
   176Ôćĺ-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** The event type to invoke
   177Ôćĺ-   `evt` **Any?** Any value (object is recommended and powerful), passed to each handler
   178Ôćĺ
   179Ôćĺ## Contribute
   181ÔćĺFirst off, thanks for taking the time to contribute!
   182ÔćĺNow, take a moment to be sure your contributions make sense to everyone else.
   183Ôćĺ
   184Ôćĺ### Reporting Issues
   186ÔćĺFound a problem? Want a new feature? First of all see if your issue or idea has [already been reported](../../issues).
   187ÔćĺIf don't, just open a [new clear and descriptive issue](../../issues/new).
   188Ôćĺ
   189Ôćĺ### Submitting pull requests
   191ÔćĺPull requests are the greatest contributions, so be sure they are focused in scope, and do avoid unrelated commits.
   192Ôćĺ
   193Ôćĺ-   Fork it!
   194Ôćĺ-   Clone your fork: `git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/mitt`
   195Ôćĺ-   Navigate to the newly cloned directory: `cd mitt`
   196Ôćĺ-   Create a new branch for the new feature: `git checkout -b my-new-feature`
   197Ôćĺ-   Install the tools necessary for development: `npm install`
   198Ôćĺ-   Make your changes.
   199Ôćĺ-   Commit your changes: `git commit -am 'Add some feature'`
   200Ôćĺ-   Push to the branch: `git push origin my-new-feature`
   201Ôćĺ-   Submit a pull request with full remarks documenting your changes.
   202Ôćĺ
